  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Surveyors",
  "description": "<p><strong>Recruitment of China Classification Society Singapore Branch:</strong><br /></p><p><strong></strong><br /></p><p><strong>Job responsibilities and job descriptions:</strong></p><p>1. Engaged in the survey of newbuilding ships, survey and audit of operating ships and offshore units, audit and certificate of suppliers, and survey of marine and offshore products;</p><p>2. Provide technical support and deal with technical problems encountered in branch inspection and audit activities;</p><p>3. Provide technical support and technical training services to customers and actively solve practical technical problems for customers;</p><p>4. Complete the training work according to the training plan and pass the examination.</p><p>5. Timely and accurately issue various certificates, survey reports and file survey files.</p><p><strong>Education Requirement:</strong></p><p>Bachelor's degree or above majoring in Marine Engineer Mechanic.<br /></p><h3>Language Proficiencies:</h3><p>English shall be fluent in listening, speaking, reading and writing.</p><p>Because of the need to face a large number of Chinese customers and Chinese flag ships, Chinese shall also be fluent in listening, speaking, reading and writing.</p><p>For non- English teaching undergraduates, English should have at least CET-4 and above qualification certificates or other equivalent English proficiency certificates. For English teaching undergraduates, O level Higher Chinese should be at least A2, Normal Chinese A1 or other equivalent Chinese proficiency certificates.</p><h3>Work Experience:</h3><p>At least 10 years on-site inspection experience in IACS member classification societies</p><h3>Qualification Certificate:</h3><p>At the same time, it has the qualifications of new shipbuilding survey, operating ship survey and audit, and marine product survey recognized by IACS member classification societies</p><h3>Competency Requirements:</h3><p>It is necessary to master the requirements of IMO conventions, classification society rules, and various survey and audit requirements and procedures. The interview exam shall be passed</p><p>Good health and physical energy, able to get on and off the ship skilfully at the anchorage</p><h3>Working Hours:</h3><p>Every Monday to Friday, from 9:00 to 18:00, it is necessary to work overtime frequently at night, on weekends and on public holidays.</p><h3>Remuneration:</h3><p>Salary: 8,000 - 10,000 SGD/ Monthly car allowance provided</p><p><br /></p><p><strong>Contact information:</strong><br />If you are interested, please send the resume and your personal contact information to kctham@ccs.org.cn, only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.</p>",
